The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 No Christmas

 Madrid, Nov 29 (Reuters): A school in traditionally Catholic Spain has cancelled Christmas celebrations so as not to offend children who are not Christians, ABC newspaper reported today.

 The Hilarion Gimeno school in Zaragoza said teachers had put forward various reasons for not celebrating Christmas, but ABC said the worry was that Muslim children might be upset. 




